file=Brand Studio/spark/operational/tool/spark-tool-requirements.md · h=name: spark-tool-requirements\ntype: operational/tool\nstatus: derived directly from instructions in each skill file\nassigned_agent: spark (Brand Studio / Creative Director — department leader)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=What each of spark's skills technically needs.\n\n**This file specifies needs — it does not grant them.** Actual access is a separate runtime-configuration step wherever spark is deployed; this table is the checklist for whoever configures it.\n · tb=\| Skill \| Required \| Optional / Future \| Source line \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| coherence-qa \| File read (kits, guides, arcs, matrix, lane results); file append (gate log, override log); **image viewing** (visual coherence judgment) \| — \| Phases 1–4 \| · tb=\| art-direction-critique \| **Image viewing** (the work under review); file read (brief/SMP) \| — \| Phase 1 "gather context"; Phase 2 axes \| · n:=- **Image viewing is load-bearing for both skills** — same caveat as atlas: without it, reviews degrade to spec-level (declared colors/type/structure) and must say so.\n- No scripts, no generation (spark judges; pixel produces), no web search (OS-level layer).\n- The gate log is append-only, following the system-wide ledger discipline.\n · h:to Apply=Image viewing + file read on the definers' documents + append on the logs is the floor.\n